Author: designer#4893
Content:
Blockchain world's last collateral asset, Bitcoin

Will Bitcoin find its role in blockchain platforms led by Samsung or IBM? those who are optimistic about blockchain but pessimistic about bitcoin predict that the coin issued by a leading company will replace bitcoin. the controversy has been around since the early days of Bitcoin. those who understand Bitcoin as a technology weigh on the prospect that Bitcoin will be replaced. 

on the other hand, those who value Bitcoin's historical significance are skeptical about the prospect of Bitcoin giving way to coin with better technology and a strong issuing entity.

not all Bitcoin attributes are inevitable. for example, the maximum amount of issuance, 21 million or an average approval time of 10 minutes, and the capacity of a block are accidental properties. However, the status of Bitcoin in blockchain phenomenon is inevitable. Whatever it was, it needed the ultimate collateral assets to boost the ecosystem of blockchain. Bitcoin is the ultimate collateral asset in a blockchain world that does not require a higher guarantor, as even ethereum began with its investment in bitcoin. Although no one guarantees this finality, Samsung, IBM, Facebook, and Google cannot replace it.
